hile downloading from Zenodo\nReturns nothing"]}, {"name": "checkm2.zenodo_backpack.zenodo_backpack_downloader._verify", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "directory", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "metadata", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "no_check_version", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Verify that a downloaded directory is in working order.\nReads <CONTENTS.json> (file) within directory containing md5 sums for files a single extracted\npayload folder with an arbitrary name\nParameters\n----------\ndirectory: str\n    Where to download to\nmetadata: json dict\n    Downloaded metadata from Zenodo containing version information\ncheck_version: True or False\n    Check version by in CONTENTS.json file matches that in Zenodo metadata\nReturns nothing if verification works, otherwise raises\nZenodoBackpackMalformedException or ZenodoBackpackVersionException"]}, {"name": "checkm2.zenodo_backpack.zenodo_backpack_downloader._retrieve_record_ID", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "DOI", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parses provided DOI retrieve associated Zenodo URL which also contains record ID\nArguments:\n    DOI (str): published DOI associated with file uploaded to Zenodo\nReturns:\n    recordID (str): last part of Zenodo url associated with DOI"]}, {"name": "checkm2.zenodo_backpack.zenodo_backpack_downloader._retrieve_record_metadata", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "recordID", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parses provided recordID to access Zenodo API records and download metadata json\nArguments:\n    recordID (str): Zenodo record number\nReturns:\n    js (json object): json metadata file retrieved from Zenodo API.\n    js['files'] (list): list of files as